tag_list: Madonna Erotica "Monsieur Adi" Remix
description: We're in a different territory. I wanted to capture eroticism in its purest form ... something tribal, dark, raw, dramatic, spiritual, and celebratory at once. The remix builds over a danceable tribal beat until it works into a huge chorus with blasting brass and twinkling synths while using a choir in a different way to provide added texture. And obviously I like a little bit of cinematic drama. So close your eyes and visualise.
title: Madonna - Erotica (Monsieur Adi Remix)

tag_list: Madonna "Get Together" "Monsieur Adi" Remix
description: A friend surprised me with the vocals to one of my favourite songs of Madonna - "Get Together." When I first heard it, I liked because it had the similar sound of "Music Sounds Better With You" by Stardust and has since been a reference for sonority. I put the song at a much slower pace to enhance the sensuality of the vocals and kept the warmth. It's impossible for me to not go a little dramatic, though. Here is the product !
title: Madonna - Get Together (Monsieur Adi Remix)

charles spencer

My Cousin Roy and many more...

The legend strikes back! Dimitri from Paris was the first DJ to pioneer house music in France in the late 80ies and became world famous with his album "Sacrebleu" in 1996. He is one of the godfathers of the "french touch" and a cult figure with dance music connoisseurs. His "Philly" and Disco compilations on BBE, Defected and Salsoul are essential and "A Night At The Playboy Mansion" (Virgin) charted in Mixmag's top 100 of best compilations ever. He remixed Björk, the Cardigans, James Brown, New Order and Quincy Jones! Dimitri teamed up with Italian DJ Rocca and Italian Cult singer Fred Ventura to create this 4 track EP for Gomma. Inspired by late 80ies/early 90ies hiphouse and electroboogie. These tracks are pure dancefloor burners. DJ Rocca (also a part of Ajello, Crimea X, Supersonic Lovers) is one of the key figures in the new Itaian House scene. Not only is he a classically trained flutist featured on "Downtown", he is also remixing for Classic, Rekids, International Feel, Modular, Luke Solomon, Blaze, Isolee, Pete Herbert and many more.
title: Erodiscotique - I NEED A REASON FOR LIVING Ft. Fred Ventura (Freestyle Edit Voc)  Snippet
